WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Chapter 1. At the beach.

00:08.000 --> 00:10.000
Hi, Kyle. How are you?

00:10.000 --> 00:12.000
Hi, Jody. Fine, thanks, you.

00:12.000 --> 00:15.000
I'm fine too, thanks.

00:15.000 --> 00:17.000
Hey! What's this?

00:17.000 --> 00:19.000
It's a tracker.

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
What's it for?

00:21.000 --> 00:22.000
Shh. Listen.

00:22.000 --> 00:23.000
What is it?

00:23.000 --> 00:25.000
I don't know.

00:25.000 --> 00:27.000
Wait a minute.

00:27.000 --> 00:29.000
What's that?

00:29.000 --> 00:31.000
Oh, it's a can.

00:31.000 --> 00:33.000
An orange juice can.

00:33.000 --> 00:35.000
Oh, Kyle, listen.

00:35.000 --> 00:37.000
There's something else here.

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
Jody. Jody, look.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.000
Look. What are they, Kyle?

00:41.000 --> 00:43.000
I don't know.

00:49.000 --> 00:53.000
Chapter 2. An exciting discovery.

00:54.000 --> 00:57.000
Are they coins?

00:57.000 --> 00:59.000
Maybe.

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
Look at the writing.

01:01.000 --> 01:02.000
Is it Spanish?

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
I don't know. Let's ask my grandpa.

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
Good idea.

01:06.000 --> 01:08.000
These coins are interesting.

01:08.000 --> 01:10.000
They look very old.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
Do you think they're valuable?

01:12.000 --> 01:14.000
Maybe.

01:14.000 --> 01:16.000
Excuse me. What's in your hand?

01:16.000 --> 01:18.000
Some coins. Have a look.

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
Are they silver?

01:20.000 --> 01:23.000
I don't know. We're going to ask my grandfather.

01:23.000 --> 01:26.000
Come on, Kyle. Let's go.

01:26.000 --> 01:29.000
Hey, kids. Do you want a drink?

01:29.000 --> 01:32.000
Kohler, orange juice, chocolate milk?

01:32.000 --> 01:35.000
Yes, please. Can we have some orange juice?

01:42.000 --> 01:46.000
Chapter 3. An accident on the beach.

01:47.000 --> 01:50.000
How much is that?

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
$1.25.

01:52.000 --> 01:53.000
Here you are.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
Thank you.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
Watch out.

01:59.000 --> 02:00.000
Are you okay?

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
My drinks. My drinks.

02:02.000 --> 02:04.000
Don't worry. They're all right.

02:04.000 --> 02:06.000
Thanks very much, kids.

02:06.000 --> 02:07.000
That's okay.

02:07.000 --> 02:09.000
You're welcome.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
Oh, Jody, I'm very excited.

02:11.000 --> 02:14.000
I think the coins are valuable.

02:14.000 --> 02:17.000
Yes. Maybe they are silver.

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
Let's go see your grandpa.

02:26.000 --> 02:30.000
Chapter 4. Are the coins valuable?

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
I have the coins.

02:37.000 --> 02:40.000
What coins? What do you mean, Beth?

02:40.000 --> 02:43.000
Look. Come on. Let's take them to my friend, Woody.

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
What do you think, Woody? Are they valuable?

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
How many coins do you have?

02:49.000 --> 02:53.000
Six. There are six coins.

02:53.000 --> 02:57.000
Hmm. These coins are silver.

02:57.000 --> 03:01.000
And they're old. They're worth a lot of money.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.000
How much money, Woody?

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
About a million dollars.

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
A million dollars.

03:08.000 --> 03:09.000
Wow!

03:09.000 --> 03:12.000
Thanks, Woody.

03:12.000 --> 03:14.000
Where are we going, Beth?

03:14.000 --> 03:16.000
To see the museum director.

03:16.000 --> 03:19.000
Now, don't say another word.

03:19.000 --> 03:21.000
Here they are, sir.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
These are wonderful.

03:23.000 --> 03:27.000
They're very old. Look at the writing. They're Spanish.

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
What else?

03:29.000 --> 03:35.000
Look, there's a Spanish ship on the man to date. 1662.

03:35.000 --> 03:37.000
Do you want the coins for your museum?

03:37.000 --> 03:40.000
Oh, yes. They're very important.

03:40.000 --> 03:42.000
Let's talk about the money.

03:48.000 --> 03:52.000
Chapter 5. The coins are missing.

03:56.000 --> 03:59.000
Grandpa! Grandpa! Where are you?

03:59.000 --> 04:01.000
Hi, Kyle. I'm in the kitchen.

04:01.000 --> 04:04.000
We have something for you to look at.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
You look excited. Is it important?

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
It's something we found on the beach.

04:09.000 --> 04:12.000
Well, let's put it on the living room table.

04:12.000 --> 04:15.000
Oh, no! Where are they?

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
What's the matter?

04:17.000 --> 04:19.000
My coins! They're gone!

04:19.000 --> 04:22.000
Are you sure? Look in your bag again.

04:22.000 --> 04:25.000
They aren't here, Jody.

04:25.000 --> 04:29.000
Calm yourself, Kyle. Try to remember where you put them.

04:29.000 --> 04:32.000
Do you want the coins, Mr. Thomas?

04:32.000 --> 04:35.000
Yes, I do. How much do you want for them?

04:35.000 --> 04:38.000
I want a million dollars.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.000
We don't have that kind of money.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
A million dollars or no deal?

04:44.000 --> 04:48.000
Okay, I can try. Come back tomorrow afternoon.

04:48.000 --> 04:53.000
If you want these coins, make sure you have the money by 2.30 tomorrow.

05:00.000 --> 05:04.000
Chapter 6. At the police station.

05:05.000 --> 05:11.000
We were on the beach. I put the coins in my bag.

05:11.000 --> 05:17.000
That's right. And then there were those two men with the drinks.

05:17.000 --> 05:23.000
That's it, Jody. They were near my bag. They have my coins.

05:23.000 --> 05:24.000
Are you sure?

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Yes, I'm sure.

05:26.000 --> 05:29.000
Let's go to the police. Come on!

05:29.000 --> 05:32.000
Can you describe the men?

05:33.000 --> 05:40.000
Yes, one man is tall and thin. He has brown hair and a beard.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
What's he wearing?

05:42.000 --> 05:47.000
A colored shirt and dark trousers. And he's wearing gym shoes.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
What about the other men?

05:49.000 --> 05:55.000
He's short and quite fat. He has blonde hair and blue eyes.

05:55.000 --> 05:59.000
He's wearing black boots, blue jeans and a white shirt.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
Can you see the two men?

06:01.000 --> 06:05.000
No, I can't. Their pictures aren't here.

06:05.000 --> 06:08.000
I'm sorry. We can't help you.

06:13.000 --> 06:18.000
Chapter 7. At the coffee shop in the mall.

06:20.000 --> 06:26.000
A million dollars. That's a lot of money, boss. What are you going to buy?

06:27.000 --> 06:31.000
Oh, a big house with a swimming pool.

06:31.000 --> 06:39.000
I want a private jet and some expensive clothes. And I want a big boat to sail around the world.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.000
What time is it?

06:41.000 --> 06:43.000
12 o'clock. Why?

06:43.000 --> 06:46.000
I'm hungry. Let's go eat something.

06:46.000 --> 06:50.000
Me too. Let's go to the coffee shop in the mall.

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
Good idea. Come on.

06:53.000 --> 06:57.000
What would you like? We want two submarine sandwiches, please.

06:57.000 --> 07:03.000
And an orange juice for me and chocolate milk for her, please.

07:03.000 --> 07:07.000
Kyle, there are the two men from the beach.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
Yikes. Jody, you're right.

07:10.000 --> 07:12.000
Where are we going now, boss?

07:12.000 --> 07:15.000
Oh, I want to think.

07:15.000 --> 07:19.000
Quick, Jody. They're leaving. Let's follow them.

07:20.000 --> 07:23.000
Get back, Jody. They mustn't see us.

07:29.000 --> 07:30.000
Chapter 8.

07:31.000 --> 07:34.000
Tall Man catches Kyle and Jody.

07:36.000 --> 07:40.000
Kyle, I can see them. They're inside.

07:40.000 --> 07:44.000
Be careful, Jody. Don't let them see us.

07:45.000 --> 07:50.000
Boss, listen. There's someone outside.

07:51.000 --> 07:54.000
Are you sure? I can't hear anything.

07:54.000 --> 07:56.000
Yeah, I heard the noise.

07:56.000 --> 07:59.000
Put me down. Get your hands off me!

08:00.000 --> 08:05.000
Well, well. The kids from the beach. What do you want?

08:05.000 --> 08:07.000
I want my coins.

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
Coins. What coins?

08:11.000 --> 08:16.000
Put them in the basement. We don't want any trouble. And tie them up.

08:16.000 --> 08:23.000
You can shelf for help if you want. But no one can hear you down here.

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
You creep!

08:26.000 --> 08:28.000
What can we do?

08:28.000 --> 08:35.000
I have an idea. There's a pen knife in my pocket. Can you get it?

08:36.000 --> 08:40.000
I can try. Can you move nearer, Jody?

08:40.000 --> 08:43.000
Okay. Now try.

08:49.000 --> 08:54.000
Chapter 9. Locked in the basement.

08:56.000 --> 09:00.000
Good afternoon. Please sit down now. About the coins.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
Do you have our money?

09:02.000 --> 09:05.000
The museum wants the coins, but we don't have enough money.

09:05.000 --> 09:10.000
Why not? I need more time. Can you come back tomorrow?

09:11.000 --> 09:15.000
I can't get it. It's too difficult.

09:15.000 --> 09:20.000
Try again, Kyle. Jody, I have the knife.

09:20.000 --> 09:24.000
Well done, Kyle. Now cut the rope.

09:24.000 --> 09:29.000
I can't do it. The rope is too thick. The knife isn't sharp enough.

09:29.000 --> 09:34.000
Press harder. That's it. We're free.

09:34.000 --> 09:39.000
We must try to escape. Come on.

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
Oh, no. We can't get out.

09:42.000 --> 09:48.000
Why? What's the matter? The door is locked. What can we do now?

09:48.000 --> 09:53.000
We have to pick the lock. We need something small.

09:53.000 --> 09:55.000
What about this coat hanger?

09:55.000 --> 10:02.000
No, it's too big. Wait. Maybe I can use my hair slide.

10:07.000 --> 10:13.000
Chapter 10. Kyle and Jody escape.

10:13.000 --> 10:18.000
We can't wait. We're going to take the coins to another museum.

10:18.000 --> 10:22.000
No. No. We want those coins for our museum.

10:22.000 --> 10:26.000
Okay, come back in one hour. I will have the money.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
You have one hour.

10:28.000 --> 10:33.000
Hello. I want the police. What are you going to do with that?

10:33.000 --> 10:38.000
Watch. Put it in the lock. Turn it.

10:38.000 --> 10:41.000
Yes, it's opening.

10:41.000 --> 10:43.000
I can hear something.

10:43.000 --> 10:47.000
Boss, I can hear a strange noise.

10:47.000 --> 10:50.000
Maybe it's those kids. Go look.

10:50.000 --> 10:57.000
Stupid kids. They can't escape. I have the key.

10:57.000 --> 11:04.000
Shut up, you kids. Don't make a noise. You can't escape from here.

11:04.000 --> 11:08.000
Yes. Don't worry, sir. We'll be good.

11:08.000 --> 11:13.000
Look at these coins, tall man. Are they real?

11:13.000 --> 11:18.000
You know they are, boss. Mr. Thomas told us that.

11:18.000 --> 11:23.000
No. They're fake, but they look like the real coins.

11:23.000 --> 11:26.000
But why do you have fake coins?

11:26.000 --> 11:31.000
Woody gave them to me. I need them for my plan.

11:35.000 --> 11:41.000
Chapter 11. Short man's plan.

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
What's your plan, boss?

11:45.000 --> 11:48.000
I'm going to sell these fake coins to the museum.

11:48.000 --> 11:51.000
What are they saying, Kyle?

11:51.000 --> 11:55.000
They're taking some fake coins to the museum.

11:55.000 --> 11:58.000
But boss, where are the real coins?

11:58.000 --> 12:02.000
They're here in a safe place in the house.

12:02.000 --> 12:06.000
What are we going to do after we get the money?

12:06.000 --> 12:09.000
We're going to take the real coins and leave town.

12:09.000 --> 12:12.000
Here are our tickets from Mexico.

12:12.000 --> 12:15.000
Now, let's go.

12:15.000 --> 12:18.000
It's okay, Jody. They're gone.

12:18.000 --> 12:20.000
Let's call the police.

12:20.000 --> 12:27.000
No, the coins first. I have an idea. Let's go get the tracker.

12:27.000 --> 12:30.000
Try the living room again.

12:30.000 --> 12:32.000
Nothing. They're not here.

12:32.000 --> 12:35.000
Let's look in the bedroom.

12:35.000 --> 12:38.000
What about under the bed or behind the cupboard?

12:39.000 --> 12:42.000
They're here near the chest of drawers.

12:42.000 --> 12:47.000
I think I know where they are. They're in the piggy bank.

12:47.000 --> 12:50.000
The silver coins.

12:50.000 --> 12:52.000
Do you have the money?

12:52.000 --> 12:56.000
Yes, here's your money. Sign your name here.

12:56.000 --> 13:00.000
Here are the silver coins. Let's go.

13:01.000 --> 13:06.000
Chapter 12. Help.

13:14.000 --> 13:17.000
Boss, the kids. They're in here.

13:17.000 --> 13:20.000
They have the coins. Quick. Get them.

13:20.000 --> 13:23.000
Jody, run to the basement door.

13:23.000 --> 13:25.000
Over here, you big gorilla.

13:25.000 --> 13:27.000
Oh! Got you.

13:27.000 --> 13:29.000
Good work, Kyle.

13:29.000 --> 13:32.000
Give me those coins, boy. Never. They're my coins.

13:32.000 --> 13:35.000
This way, Kyle. Hurry!

13:35.000 --> 13:39.000
Help me! Help! Help!

13:41.000 --> 13:43.000
Let the boy go. Now.

13:43.000 --> 13:46.000
You are under arrest. We're taking you to the police station.

13:46.000 --> 13:50.000
Okay. Okay, guys. He's not hurt.

13:51.000 --> 14:00.000
Chapter 13. A happy ending.

14:04.000 --> 14:08.000
You two are going to prison for a very long time.

14:08.000 --> 14:10.000
That was pesky kids.

14:10.000 --> 14:13.000
Are we going to Mexico now, boss?

14:13.000 --> 14:16.000
Look, Kyle, you and Jody are famous.

14:16.000 --> 14:19.000
Your story is in the newspaper. Let me see.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.000
Look, Jody, there's a photo, too.

14:22.000 --> 14:26.000
Thanks to you, Kyle and Jody, those two crooks are locked up in prison.

14:26.000 --> 14:30.000
And these important coins are safe in the museum.

14:30.000 --> 14:34.000
Can you tell us something about the coins, Mr. Thomas?

14:34.000 --> 14:39.000
They are very old and rare coins. They come from a Spanish ship.

14:39.000 --> 14:48.000
Its name was the Atacha. In the autumn of 1662, on the 4th of September, it left Cuba for Spain.

14:48.000 --> 14:51.000
There were a lot of precious things on the ship.

14:51.000 --> 14:57.000
There were 400 bars of gold and 120,000 silver coins.

14:57.000 --> 15:02.000
There were pearl necklaces and bracelets, rings and gold plates.

15:02.000 --> 15:05.000
But the weather was bad and the ship was in trouble.

15:05.000 --> 15:10.000
It sank to the bottom of the ocean and all the precious things were lost.

15:10.000 --> 15:16.000
The legend says that the ship is still there, under the sea near the Florida coast.

15:16.000 --> 15:22.000
Sometimes silver coins are found on the beaches near the ship, washed up by the waves.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.000
What are you going to do with the reward, Money, Kyle?

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
I'm going to buy a bigger tracker.

15:28.000 --> 15:30.000
Are you crazy? Why?

15:30.000 --> 15:36.000
There were 120,000 coins on the Atocha. We found six.

15:36.000 --> 15:43.000
I want to find the other 119,994. Do you want to help me?

15:43.000 --> 15:50.000
No thanks. It's too dangerous. I'm going to play beach volleyball. It's safer.

